<h3>Collecting information about you</h3>
<p>We may collect information about your computer and your visits to the Site and this may include your IP address, referrer URL (if provided), geographical location, browser type, length of visit and number of pages views.  We may use this information for a number of purposes such as optimising the use of the Site or for security purposes.  In particular, we may use an analytics service provider for website traffic analysis and reporting and to track information such as which browser, screen resolution and IP address you are using to access our website, in addition, to tracing your movements around our website.  We collect this information to help us diagnose problems and administer our systems and to audit the geographical make up of users and how they have arrived at our site; that is what other sites have visitors arrived – this information being obtained from the referrer URL.  </p>

<p>We do not normally link IP addresses to anything personally identifiable, which means that you remain anonymous even though we include your IP address in our aggregate information.  However, we can and will attempt to use IP addresses to identify a user when we feel it is necessary to enforce compliance with our terms and conditions, or to protect our services and other users. </p>

